<div id="sidehead">Budget Allotment </div><br>
	<li>The HCD receives 40 % of the total budget allotment in each financial year. </li>
<br><b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:20">Process Description</b><br><br>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Any student who wants to approach HCD for Medical help has to fill in the application form (Pl find the attachment in Annex – I) and submit it to the class HH representative. The application forms will be available with the cluster/floor/branch level HH representatives. All applications will be scrutinized at four levels.
</p>
<li>Duly filled application has to be submit along with the required documents and two neighbour class HH representative sign to the class HH representative. If the class HH representative, upon scrutiny, is satisfied with claims of the applicant he/she will forward the application to the respective cluster/floor/branch HH representative. </li>
<br>
<li>If the cluster/floor, branch representative, upon scrutiny, is satisfied with the claims of the applicant he/she will forward the application to the respective class/branch EC member. </li>
<br>
<li>If the EC member finds that the case is genuine he/she will personally handover the application to the Joint Secretory of HCD.</li>
<br>
<li>The Joint secretory of HCD after verifying the application approves the amount of financial grant to be provided and forwards the application to the finance dept. The finance dept., based on the recommendations of the Joint secretory of HCD will disburse the grant to a student.</li>
<br>
<li>Sanction money if more than 5000 Rs. then the Joint secretory of HCD need to arrange EC meeting after consulting with General Secretary for necessary approval.</li>
<br>
<li>If an application successfully reaches the Joint secretory of HCD it means that the application is consider for final acceptance unless the Joint secretory strongly feels for a fresh scrutiny.  The class HH representative, cluster/floor, branch representatives and the EC members have to carefully verify the case before forwarding it to the next level. </li>
<br>
<li>An EC member from HCD will personally handover the applications to the Joint secretory/representative of finance dept. Finance dept. will release fund after verification and send back the application through finance representative to HCD for documentation. </li>
<br>
<b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:16"><blink>
<u>Note</u></blink></b>
<b style="font-size:14">Note: Cluster rep. for PUC, Floor rep. for E-1 and Brach rep. for E-2, E-3 and E-4.</b><br><br>
<li>Conduct General & Expert Health camps periodically and Outside Charity in terms of Health case Joint Secretory of HCD need to arrange EC meeting after consulting with General Secretary for necessary approval.</li>

<br><b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:20">For Students</b><br><br>

<li>Any student who wants to approach Health Care Department (HCD) for help have to fill the application (Available with the cluster/floor/branch HH representative) and attach copies of the required documents.</li>
<br>
<li>
The duly filled application has to be submit along with the required documents and two neighbour class HH representative sign to the class HH representative. The application will be processed through class HH representative and to cluster/floor/branch representative and to student EC member and finally to the Joint secretory of HCD. 
</li>
<br>
<li>
If required applicant may need to present himself/herself before the Joint secretory of HCD.
</li>

<h5>Documents Needed</h5>
<p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Photo copies/Xerox of the following documents have to be attached along with the application.
</p>
<li>Income certificate/white ration card</li>
<li>College ID proof </li>
<li>Proof of Prescription or report given by Doctors (Preferable M.S or MD)</li>
<li>Proof of Bills need to submit after completion of treatment.</li>

<br><b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:20">For Class HH Representative</b><br><br>
<li>The Class HH Representative have to guide the students regarding where the applications are available (applications are with the cluster/floor/branch HH representatives). </li><br>
<li>Help the applicant in completing the form, if needed.</li><br>
<li>HH Representative is required to receive the filled application along with the needed attachments from the applicant and scrutinize it. </li>
<li>HH Representative has to verify whether all details in the application are completed and all the necessary proofs are attached along with sign. </li><br>
<li>If HH Representative finds that the case is genuine then he/she has to personally submit them to respective cluster/floor/branch HH representative. </li><br>
<li>HH Representative has to scrutinize the application within <b>one working day</b>.</li>

<br><b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:20">For Cluster/Floor/Branch HH Representatives</b><br><br>
<li>You have to maintain application forms with you and should make them available to the students.</li><br>
<li>The filled in applications forms will be forwarded to you from the class HH representatives with their signature. </li><br>
<li>You may need to meet the class rep. to verify the case and if you are satisfied you have to personally submit the application with your signature to the respective EC member. </li><br>
<li>If you are not satisfied with the case please return the application to the class HH rep. stating your doubts.</li><br>
<li>You have to process the application to the next level within one working day.</li><br>
<li>PUC cluster representative have to submit the application to…</li><br>
