<br><b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:20">For HCD EC Members</b><br><br>
<li>EC Members will receive the filled application from the respective cluster/floor/branch HH rep.</li>
<li>EC Members are required to verify the facts mentioned in the application.</li>
<li>EC Members may meet class rep. or cluster/floor/branch rep. if needed.</li>
<li>If EC Members are satisfied he/she have to personally submit to the Joint secretory of HCD.</li>
<li>If EC Members are not satisfied he/she have to return the application to the class HH rep.</li>
<li>EC Members have to process the application in one working day.</li>
<br><b style="margin-left:15px;margin-right:50px;font-size:20">For the Joint secretory of HCD</b><br><br>
<li>Joint secretory will receive the applications from the respective student EC members.</li>
<li>Joint secretory will endorse to finance dept to release the fund by keeping the record in proper category wise and are required to process the applications in one working day.</li>
<li>If Joint secretory strongly feel that further scrutiny is needed then he/she may take necessary steps in this regard.</li>
<li>Track the record of allocated budget.</li><br>
<div id="sidehead">Rules and regulations</div><br>
<li>HCD will consult other faculty EC members & Advisory committee , in case it has to extend its services to the people other than the student (parents, relatives, staff) as an exceptional case</li><br>
<li>HCD responsibility is strictly restricted to student’s health issues not their parents, relatives or any other staff / Faculty members in the campus.</li><br>
<li>HCD generally not responsible for the accidents happened outside the campus. However the situation will be viewed in humanitarian grounds & it may extend its support in all the possible & eligible cases</li><br>
<li>HCD never ensure the full reimbursement / full payment for treatment or medicine. Student has to bare some minimum amount from his personal front. However this minimum amount varies from case to case.</li><br>
<li>Preference is given only for the RGUKT Nuzvid campus students. In this regard maximum 1/10th of total medical allocation will be provide per student, during serious case maximum limit will be change according to severity of case and it will be decide by only EC meeting.</li><br>
<li>Necessary proofs have to produce for utilizing the medical allowance. (i.e. Medical report/prescription given by M.S/M.D/highly educated Doctors) otherwise application will be rejected.</li><br>
<li>Medical allowance sanctioned students should have to produce bills during or after the treatment and one zerox copy of certificate and bill need to submit to committee otherwise next time medical help will not be entitle to him/her.</li><br>
<li>Sanction money if more than 1000 Rs. then transaction should be in check form only.</li><br>
<li>Students, who are suffering with “long term diseases”, have to renewal every academic year and separate file will be maintain for them and grant will be sanction maximum of  4 years only.</li><br>
